---
<style>
  .mobile-section-grid { display: grid; gap: 2rem; }
  @media (min-width: 768px) { .mobile-section-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }

  .mobile-grid { display: grid; gap: 2rem; align-items: center; }
  @media (min-width: 768px) { .mobile-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; } }

  .phone-wrap { position: relative; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; }
  .phone-wrap::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: -20px;
    border-radius: 2rem;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse at center, rgba(78,222,163,0.15) 0%, rgba(173,198,255,0.08) 50%, transparent 70%);
    filter: blur(20px);
    z-index: 0;
  }
  .phone-img {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    border-radius: 1.25rem; overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.5), 0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    transform: rotate(2deg); transition: transform 0.5s ease;
    width: 100%; max-width: 180px; margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .phone-img:hover { transform: rotate(0deg) scale(1.02); }
  .phone-img img { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }

  /* Mobile: stack image on top, text below */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .mobile-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .order-img { order: 0 !important; }
    .order-text { order: 1 !important; }
    .phone-img { max-width: 140px; }
    .card-pad { padding: 1.25rem !important; }
    .section-title { font-size: 28px !important; margin-bottom: 1.5rem !important; }
  }
</style>

<section class="py-section-padding-desktop reveal" style="background:rgba(50,53,60,0.1)">
  <div class="px-gutter max-w-container-max mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-headline-lg section-title" style="color:var(--color-on-surface);margin-bottom:3rem">Mobile Innovation</h2>

    <!-- Project 1: Smart Walking Cane -->
    <div class="glass-card mobile-grid card-pad" style="padding:1.5rem 2rem;border-radius:1.5rem;margin-bottom:2rem">
      <div class="order-text" style="order:2">
        <h3 class="text-headline-md" style="color:var(--color-on-surface);margin-bottom:1rem">Smart Walking Cane</h3>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:1.5rem">
          {['Kotlin','Firebase','IoT'].map(t => <span class="tech-chip text-label-sm" style="padding:4px 12px;border-radius:9999px;white-space:nowrap">{t}</span>)}
        </div>
        <p class="text-body-lg" style="color:var(--color-on-surface-variant)">
          Experienced in developing an IoT-based Smart Walking Cane (SWC) for elderly users as part of a student project at Universitas Pendidikan Indonesia (UPI). The SWC is an assistive device built using PVC pipe as the cane structure, modem, electrical box, switch, ESP32, GPS module, SOS button, and additional supporting components, designed to enhance user safety and enable remote monitoring and control via smartphone. The system allows caregivers or family members to monitor and control the device remotely to help keep users safe in daily activities. In this project, I served as Mobile Frontend Developer while also handling IoT feature integration for remote monitoring and control. Experienced in mobile app development, ESP32 integration, GPS modules, and implementing IoT-based monitoring systems and embedded systems according to user needs.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="phone-wrap order-img" style="order:1">
        <div class="phone-img">
          <img alt="Smart Walking Cane UI" src="/smartwalkingcane.jpg" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Project 2: Delta App -->
    <div class="glass-card mobile-grid card-pad" style="padding:1.5rem 2rem;border-radius:1.5rem">
      <div class="order-text" style="order:1">
        <h3 class="text-headline-md" style="color:var(--color-on-surface);margin-bottom:1rem">Delta – Customer Service Digitalization System</h3>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:1.5rem">
          {['Flutter','Dart','OpenStreetMap API','JWT Auth','REST API'].map(t => <span class="tech-chip text-label-sm" style="padding:4px 12px;border-radius:9999px;white-space:nowrap">{t}</span>)}
        </div>
        <p class="text-body-lg" style="color:var(--color-on-surface-variant)">
          Designed and built an Android application using Flutter as the primary digitalization solution for PT. Delta Solusi Internet's self-service platform. The project automates the entire administrative workflow, from installation request features powered by OpenStreetMap API and real-time progress tracking to a billing payment module. Implemented key features including an Interactive Dashboard, Package Management, Billing System, Trouble Ticketing, Referral & Commission Program, and Profile Management, with REST API integration using JWT Authentication.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="phone-wrap order-img" style="order:2">
        <div class="phone-img">
          <img alt="Delta App UI" src="/delta.jpeg" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Project 3: SIMORA Android -->
    <div class="glass-card mobile-grid card-pad" style="padding:1.5rem 2rem;border-radius:1.5rem;margin-top:2rem">
      <div class="order-text" style="order:2">
        <h3 class="text-headline-md" style="color:var(--color-on-surface);margin-bottom:1rem">SIMORA Android – Company Car Booking System</h3>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:8px;margin-bottom:1.5rem">
          {['Flutter','Dart','Laravel PHP','MySQL'].map(t => <span class="tech-chip text-label-sm" style="padding:4px 12px;border-radius:9999px;white-space:nowrap">{t}</span>)}
        </div>
        <p class="text-body-lg" style="color:var(--color-on-surface-variant)">
          Developed an Android mobile application as a companion app for the company car booking system at PT. Belaputera Intiland, featuring a modern UI, smooth animations, and gradient design. The app supports dual-role authentication (Employee and Driver) integrated with a web backend, complete with a mobile dashboard, booking management for employees, task management for drivers, and real-time push notifications. Key features include GPS tracking, rating system, profile management, and history tracking.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="phone-wrap order-img" style="order:1">
        <div class="phone-img">
          <img alt="SIMORA Android UI" src="/simoraandro.png" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
